## Common C++ Patterns

### Event Handling & References
When passing events or objects to functions expecting lvalue references:

❌ Don't:
```cpp
someFunction(EventClass()); // Error: temporary/rvalue cannot bind to non-const reference
```
✅ Do:
```cpp
EventClass evt; // Create named object (lvalue)
someFunction(evt); // Pass the named object
```

